Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of graph classes defined by forbidden induced subgraphs and their clique-width. This topic falls under the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithmic consequences of the results, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) or computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper considers classes characterized by forbidding a finite family of graphs as subgraphs, minors, and topological minors, which could fall under graph theory (cs.GT).
